  "local_port": 41426,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some great dinner ideas for a sleepover?",
  "response": "Planning a dinner for a sleepover should be fun, easy, and interactive! Here are some great ideas that will satisfy everyone and add to the fun:\n\n### **Finger Foods & Snack Platters**\n1. **Build-Your-Own Nachos/Tacos**  \n   - Tortilla chips or taco shells  \n   - Ground beef, chicken, or beans  \n   - Cheese, guacamole, salsa, sour cream, and other toppings  \n   - Let everyone customize their plate!\n\n2. **Pizza Bar**  \n   - Pre-made pizza dough or flatbreads  \n   - Assorted toppings (pepperoni, veggies, cheese, etc.)  \n   - Let everyone create their own mini pizzas.\n\n3. **Sliders Board**  \n   - Mini burger buns or Hawaiian rolls  \n   - Beef patties, chicken tenders, or veggie patties  \n   - Toppings like cheese, pickles, lettuce, and sauces.\n\n4. **Charcuterie Board**  \n   - Sliced meats, cheeses, crackers, olives, nuts, and dips.  \n   - Add some fruit (grapes, berries) for a sweet touch.\n\n---\n\n### **Interactive Meals**\n5. **DIY Pasta Bar**  \n   - Cooked pasta (penne, spaghetti, etc.)  \n   - Sauces (marinara, Alfredo, pesto)  \n   - Toppings (meatballs, mushrooms, spinach, etc.).\n\n6. **Stuffed Potato Bar**  \n   - Baked potatoes or sweet potatoes  \n   - Toppings like cheese, bacon, sour cream, chives, and chili.\n\n7. **Sushi Roll Night**  \n   - Sushi rice, nori sheets, and fillings (cucumber, avocado, crab, etc.)  \n   - Let everyone roll their own sushi!\n\n---\n\n### **Fun & Comforting Classics**\n8. **Mac and Cheese Bar**  \n   - Creamy mac and cheese with mix-ins like bacon, broccoli, or buffalo chicken.\n\n9. **Breakfast for Dinner**  \n   - Pancakes, waffles, or French toast  \n   - Toppings like syrup, whipped cream, and fruit.\n\n10. **Chili & Cornbread**  \n    - Serve with toppings like shredded cheese, sour cream, and green onions.\n\n---\n\n### **Dessert Ideas**\n11. **Ice Cream Sundae Bar**  \n    - Vanilla, chocolate, and strawberry ice cream  \n    - Toppings like sprinkles, chocolate sauce, and cherries.\n\n12. **Mini Desserts**  \n    - Brownie bites, cookies, or cupcakes for easy sharing.\n\n---\n\n### **Drinks**\n13. **Mocktails**  \n    - Fancy non-alcoholic drinks like Shirley Temples or fruit punch.\n\n14. **Hot Chocolate Bar**  \n    - Set up with marshmallows, whipped cream, and flavored syrups.\n\n---\n\nThe key is to keep it simple, communal, and fun! Let everyone get involved in the preparation or assembly for a memorable sleepover dinner.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
